headline: U.S. Treasuries Stabilize as Investors Stay Cautious Despite Government Reopening
summary: U.S. Treasury yields stabilize in European mid-morning hours, having risen earlier on news that the U.S. government is set to reopen as caution creeps in.  "Markets remain cautious as attention shifts to the backlog of economic data soon to be released, which could paint a softer picture of the labor market and overall demand," says Exness' Eric Chia in a note.  The two-year Treasury yield rises 0.8 basis points to 3.573%; the 10-year Treasury yield is unchanged at 4.078%; and the 30-year yield stays steady at 4.662%, Tradeweb data show.
